When a user is inside configurations and look for intelli-sense, it would be good to provide existing configuration names

#16026

Have the following valid JSON `launch.json` file:

```
{
  // Use IntelliSense to learn about possible Node.js debug attributes.
  // Hover to view descriptions of existing attributes.
  // For more information, visit: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=830387
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations":
   [
    {
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "name": "Launch Program",
      "program": "${workspaceRoot}/bin/www",
      "cwd": "${workspaceRoot}"
    },
    {
      "type": "node",
      "request": "attach",
      "name": "Attach to Process",
      "port": 5858
    }
  ]
}
```

Click `Add Configuration` and pick one. It will create a syntactically wrong file.
